sys_hub_flow.description:
This flow is designed to retrieve services data from the SAP ECC system.

Inputs:

  • Service Record - This input is an integration service job tracker record that contains the details about the executed service or job.
  • Connection Name - This input is a Connection and Credential alias record used to connect to the target system.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "1", if the request is "Success" or will be set to "2", if the request is "Error”.
  • Error - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

To use this subflow, the corresponding SAP ECC - RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP ECC Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_flow_snapshot.description:
This flow is designed to retrieve services data from the SAP ECC system.

Inputs:

  • Service Record - This input is an integration service job tracker record that contains the details about the executed service or job.
  • Connection Name - This input is a Connection and Credential alias record used to connect to the target system.

Outputs:

  • Status - Will be set to "1", if the request is "Success" or will be set to "2", if the request is "Error”.
  • Error - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

To use this subflow, the corresponding SAP ECC - RFC connection and credential must be created and associated with the SAP ECC Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
